{
  "texts": [
    "Each of these cycles or edges is treated as a cluster.",
    "Subsequently, a cluster graph is constructed by adding edges between all intersecting clusters.",
    "Finally, one of its spanning trees is selected as the connection tree for G. Due to cycle merging, any two clusters in the connection tree share at most two common atoms.",
    "Francois Berenger and Koji Tsuda proposed another fragmentation logic based on molecular structures in FASMIFRA 29.",
    "FASMIFRA performs molecular fragmentation by identifying bonds between heavy atoms which not in rings that can be cleaved."
  ]
}